F3232-bit floating-point number.F32.to_reprRound-trippable repr (9 sig digits): str.to_f32(x.to_repr()) == x.F32.from_i64Convert from I64 to F32.F32.safe_divDivision that throws DivideByZero when dividing by zero.\nReuses the DivideByZero type from src/core/i64.til.\nUse F32.div for the silent (NaN/Inf) variant.U64Unsigned 64-bit integer.U64.to_strConvert to decimal string representation.U64.unityReturn the multiplicative identity (1) for this type.U64.distanceAbsolute difference between two values, useful for Range iteration.U64.safe_addAddition that throws IntegerOverflow on unsigned wrap.\nUse U64.add for the wrapping variant.U64.safe_subSubtraction that throws IntegerOverflow when a < b (underflow\nwraps unsigned). Use U64.sub for the wrapping variant.U64.safe_mulMultiplication that throws IntegerOverflow on unsigned wrap.\nUse U64.mul for the wrapping variant.U32Unsigned 32-bit integer.U32.to_strConvert to decimal string representation.U32.unityReturn the multiplicative identity (1) for this type.U32.distanceAbsolute difference between two values, useful for Range iteration.U32.safe_addAddition that throws IntegerOverflow on unsigned wrap.\nUse U32.add for the wrapping variant.U32.safe_subSubtraction that throws IntegerOverflow when a < b (underflow\nwraps unsigned). Use U32.sub for the wrapping variant.U32.safe_mulMultiplication that throws IntegerOverflow on unsigned wrap.\nUse U32.mul for the wrapping variant.I32Signed 32-bit integer.I32.to_strConvert to decimal string representation.I32.unityReturn the multiplicative identity (1) for this type.I32.negNegate the value.I32.absAbsolute value.I32.distanceAbsolute difference between two values, useful for Range iteration.I32.safe_addAddition that throws IntegerOverflow on signed wrap.\nUse I32.add for the wrapping variant.I32.safe_subSubtraction that throws IntegerOverflow on signed wrap.\nUse I32.sub for the wrapping variant.I32.safe_mulMultiplication that throws IntegerOverflow on signed wrap.\nUse I32.mul for the wrapping variant.I8Signed 8-bit integer.I8.to_strConvert to decimal string representation.I8.unityReturn the multiplicative identity (1) for this type.I8.negNegate the value.I8.absAbsolute value.I8.distanceAbsolute difference between two values, useful for Range iteration.U8Unsigned 8-bit integer.U8.to_strConvert to decimal string representation.U8.unityReturn the multiplicative identity (1) for this type.U8.distanceAbsolute difference between two values, useful for Range iteration.U8.safe_addAddition that throws IntegerOverflow on unsigned wrap.\nUse U8.add for the wrapping variant.U8.safe_subSubtraction that throws IntegerOverflow when a < b (underflow\nwraps unsigned). Use U8.sub for the wrapping variant.U8.safe_mulMultiplication that throws IntegerOverflow on unsigned wrap.\nUse U8.mul for the wrapping variant.VecDynamic array of typed elements.Array__Dynamic.newCreate a zero-initialized Array with the given capacity.Array__Dynamic.getRef to the element at index `i`. Throws OutOfBounds if `i` is\npast the end; call as `arr.get(i)!` to panic on a bad index.Array__Dynamic.setOverwrite the element at index `i`. Drops the old value. `val` is\nowned. Throws OutOfBounds if `i` is past the end; call as\n`arr[i] = val` (or `arr.set(i, own val)!`) to panic on a bad index.\n(Codegen that fills a fresh in-bounds slot uses set_init, below.)Array__Dynamic.set_initNon-throwing in-place set used by the variadic-argument codegen\n(build_variadic_array_set fills a freshly-allocated, in-bounds slot\nfor every variadic call). Once `set` starts throwing OutOfBounds --\nso `arr[i] = v` can desugar to `arr.set(i, own v)!` -- the variadic\ncodegen must not call the throwing `set` (the typer emits these\nafter throws-lowering, so they would never get the err-args). This\nvariant panics on a bad index instead of throwing, keeping the\ncodegen decoupled from `set`'s signature.formatConcatenate multiple strings into one.StrUTF-8 string with owned heap storage. The byte buffer is typed as\nI8 (= C `char`) so direct FFI bindings against `const char *` APIs\ncan pass `s.c_str` without an intermediate pointer-cast helper.Str.getReturn a ref to byte `i`. Panics if `i` is out of bounds.Str.byte_atUnchecked byte access -- caller must ensure i < self.len().Str.cmpLexicographic comparison. Returns 0 if equal, negative if a < b,\npositive if a > b.Str.concatReturn a new Str with the contents of `a` followed by `b`.Str.with_capacityCreate an empty Str pre-allocated for up to `n` bytes.Str.from_c_strWrap a NUL-terminated C string as a non-owning Str view (no copy).\nThe view borrows `s`; the caller keeps ownership of the buffer.Str.push_strAppend `s` to `self`. Panics if `self` is a view/literal or if\ncapacity is exceeded.Str.cloneDeep-copy the string into a new owned Str.Str.to_strString representation of a Str: a fresh owned copy of itself. Lets\nStr satisfy the same `T.to_str(x)` contract as the numeric types, so\ngeneric code (e.g. assert_eq(Str, a, b)) works uniformly.Str.deleteFree the backing buffer unless it is borrowed/static. CAP_LIT names a\nstatic literal wrapper, so call_free does not free that wrapper either.Str.substrReturn a view into `s` from `start` for `n` bytes (no allocation).\nClamps to valid bounds.Str.trim_startReturn a view of `s` with leading ASCII whitespace (space, tab,\nnewline, carriage return) removed. View-only -- no allocation.Str.trimReturn a view of `s` with leading and trailing ASCII whitespace\nremoved. View-only -- no allocation.Str.containsTrue if `a` contains `b` as a substring.Str.starts_withTrue if `a` starts with prefix `b`.Str.ends_withTrue if `a` ends with suffix `b`.Str.is_emptyTrue if the string has zero length.Str.findReturn the byte index of the first occurrence of `needle`, or -1.Str.rfindReturn the byte index of the last occurrence of `needle`, or -1.Str.replaceReturn a new Str with all occurrences of `from` replaced by `to`.Str.get_charView of the single byte at index `i` as a Str.Str.hashHash via the caller-supplied byte hasher, feeding it the\nstring CONTENT bytes (c_str + count). The default bytewise\nfallback would hash the {c_str, count, cap} struct itself --\ni.e. the heap pointer's address -- which is identity, not\nequality. The container chooses the algorithm; this method\nchooses the right bytes for a Str.Str.strip_prefixIf self starts with `prefix`, return the rest; otherwise clone.Str.strip_suffixIf self ends with `suffix`, return the part before it; otherwise clone.Str.from_byteCreate a 1-byte Str from a U8 value.Str.to_i64Parse the string as a signed integer. Accepts an optional leading\n'-', base prefixes 0x/0b/0o (issue #255), and '_' digit separators.\nBare digit runs are base-10. Panics on invalid input.Str.to_u8Parse as base-10 unsigned 8-bit integer.Str.to_i8Parse as base-10 signed 8-bit integer.Str.to_i16Parse as base-10 signed 16-bit integer.Str.to_u16Parse as base-10 unsigned 16-bit integer.Str.to_i32Parse as base-10 signed 32-bit integer.Str.to_u32Parse as base-10 unsigned 32-bit integer.Str.to_u64Parse as base-10 unsigned 64-bit integer.Str.to_usizeParse as base-10 USize (collection sizes/indices).Str.to_f32Parse as a floating-point number. Backed by C strtof: handles\ndecimal and scientific notation at full precision, so a value\nprinted by F32.to_repr round-trips exactly back to the same F32.\n'_' digit separators (issue #255) are stripped first since strtof\ndoes not accept them.Str.splitSplit the string on `delim`, returning a Vec of Str clones.OutOfBoundsError thrown by the indexed collection accessors (Array.get,\nVec.get, ...) when the index is past the end. The msg field\ncarries a \"file:line:col:<method>: index N out of bounds (len M)\"\ndescription set at the throw site.KeyNotFoundError type for keyed accessors (Map.get, HashMap.get, ...) when\nthe key is not present. The msg field carries a\n\"file:line:col:<method>: key not found\" description set at the\nthrow site.Array__Str.newCreate a zero-initialized Array with the given capacity.Array__Str.getRef to the element at index `i`. Throws OutOfBounds if `i` is\npast the end; call as `arr.get(i)!` to panic on a bad index.Array__Str.setOverwrite the element at index `i`. Drops the old value. `val` is\nowned. Throws OutOfBounds if `i` is past the end; call as\n`arr[i] = val` (or `arr.set(i, own val)!`) to panic on a bad index.\n(Codegen that fills a fresh in-bounds slot uses set_init, below.)Array__Str.set_initNon-throwing in-place set used by the variadic-argument codegen\n(build_variadic_array_set fills a freshly-allocated, in-bounds slot\nfor every variadic call). Once `set` starts throwing OutOfBounds --\nso `arr[i] = v` can desugar to `arr.set(i, own v)!` -- the variadic\ncodegen must not call the throwing `set` (the typer emits these\nafter throws-lowering, so they would never get the err-args). This\nvariant panics on a bad index instead of throwing, keeping the\ncodegen decoupled from `set`'s signature.Vec__Str.newCreate a new empty Vec for elements of type T.Vec__Str.clearDrop all live elements via elem_delete but keep the allocated\nstorage and element-type metadata so the Vec can be reused.Vec__Str.pushAppend an element to the end. `val` is owned: after this call the\ncaller must not use the value passed -- clone it first if needed.Vec__Str.appendConsume the contents of `other` by appending them to `self`.\n`other` is taken by ownership and will be empty after the call.Vec__Str.move_fromReplace self's contents with other's via memcpy (no per-elem clone).\nAvoids the Vec_clone + extra Vec_delete that plain `self = other` emits.\nTakes `mut` (not `own`) so caller retains ownership of other; its\nnatural scope-end auto-delete frees other.data. Setting other.count = 0\nprevents that auto-delete from re-running elem_delete on items whose\nbytes were moved into self.Vec__Str.getReturn a reference to the element at index `i`. Throws\nOutOfBounds if `i` is past the end; call as `vec[i]`\nto panic on a bad index. The reference is valid until the\nnext mutation.Vec__Str.popRemove and return the last element. Panics if empty. The caller\ntakes ownership of the returned value.Vec__Str.take_prefixSplit off the first `n` elements into a new Vec. Panics if `n`\nexceeds self.len(). The remaining elements shift to the front.Vec__Str.setOverwrite the element at index `i`. `val` is owned. Throws\nOutOfBounds if `i` is past the end; call as `vec[i] = val`\n(or `vec.set(i, own val)!`) to panic on a bad index.Vec__Str.push_takeMove bytes of src[i] into self (push). Source slot is zeroed so that\nsrc's eventual elem_delete on it is a no-op (relies on the same\ncount==0/data==NULL convention used by take_children and Vec.delete).Vec__Str.deleteDrop each element via elem_delete, free storage, then free self\nunless `call_free` is false.Vec__Str.cloneDeep-copy the Vec and all its elements via elem_clone.I16Signed 16-bit integer.I16.to_strConvert to decimal string representation.I16.unityReturn the multiplicative identity (1) for this type.I16.negNegate the value.I16.absAbsolute value.I16.distanceAbsolute difference between two values, useful for Range iteration.I16.safe_addAddition that throws IntegerOverflow on signed wrap.\nUse I16.add for the wrapping variant.I16.safe_subSubtraction that throws IntegerOverflow on signed wrap.\nUse I16.sub for the wrapping variant.I16.safe_mulMultiplication that throws IntegerOverflow on signed wrap.\nUse I16.mul for the wrapping variant.I64Signed 64-bit integer.I64.to_usizeConvert to USize (target-width unsigned integer). Backed by the\nC-level cast (USize)val so it tracks ext.h's USize typedef once it\nbecomes target-driven on 64-bit; see issue #192.I64.unityReturn the multiplicative identity (1) for this type.I64.negNegate the value.I64.absAbsolute value.I64.distanceAbsolute difference between two values, useful for Range iteration.I64.safe_divIssue #198: division that throws DivideByZero when dividing by\nzero. Use I64.div for the panicking variant.I64.safe_addAddition that throws IntegerOverflow on signed wrap.\nUse I64.add for the wrapping variant.I64.safe_subSubtraction that throws IntegerOverflow on signed wrap.\nUse I64.sub for the wrapping variant.I64.safe_mulMultiplication that throws IntegerOverflow on signed wrap.\nUse I64.mul for the wrapping variant.DivideByZeroError thrown by I64.safe_div when dividing by zero.IntegerOverflowError thrown by safe_add / safe_sub / safe_mul on the integer\ntypes when the operation would wrap. Carries a\n\"file:line:col:<method>: a OP b overflows/underflows\" msg. One\nshared type for all integer widths.BoolBoolean value: true or false.Bool.to_strReturn \"true\" or \"false\".Bool.cmpComparison: false < true. Returns 0, -1, or 1.MapOrdered map from typed keys to typed values.PrimitiveReal primitive types. Issue #203 migrates them one at a time;\nI16 first because it has the smallest call-site surface.TypeType representation for the til compiler. Carries payload for named\ntypes (Struct/Enum/Custom) and is tag-only for builtins.FuncTypeClassifies a til function declaration: func, proc, test, macro, or external.OwnTypeArgument ownership mode: Own (takes ownership), Ref (borrow), Shallow (trivial copy).DeclarationVariable/field/parameter declaration node.FunctionDefFunction signature metadata: params, return type, variadic info.FCallDataPer-callsite data for function calls: parse-time flags (is_splat,\ndoes_throw, is_bang), own_args bitmap, result type. The variadic\nand kwargs block positions and counts are not stored -- they all\nderive from the resolved callee's param layout plus the structural\nmarkers in fcall.children:\n  - kwargs_count : trailing-NamedArg count (fcall_kwargs_count).\n  - kwargs_index : derived position via fcall_kwargs_index_via_scope.\n  - variadic_count : children layout + nparam + has-kwargs\n    (fcall_variadic_count).\n  - variadic_index : implicit at `1 + fdef_data.variadic_index`\n    post-desugar. Step 7 of #147 closes here: the trailing typer\n    resolution artifact is gone.StructDefStruct definition: field declarations, namespace methods, c_tag.\nIssue #147 step 4: total_struct_size dropped from the AST in favour\nof ctx.struct_layouts[name].total_size, populated by\ncompute_struct_layout at typer time.EnumDefEnum definition: variants, payload types, namespace methods.\nIssue #147 step 4: total_enum_size dropped from the AST in favour\nof ctx.struct_layouts[name].total_size, populated by\ncompute_enum_layout at typer time.AssignDataPayload for assignment nodes: which name is being assigned to.ForInDataPayload for `for name in range` loop nodes.LiteralLiteral (constant) node kinds: the leaf values written directly in\nsource. Grouped under NodeType.Literal so \"is this any literal?\"\nis a single check (NodeType.Literal) instead of a four-way chain.MatchDataPayload for NodeType.Match: a `match` expression yields a value, so\nthe typer records the common arm type here (mirrors FCallData.til_type).CaptureBlockDataPayload for NodeType.CaptureBlock (issue #54): a bare `[a, mut b] { ... }`\nblock carrying an explicit capture list. The captures restrict which\nouter-scope locals the block body may reference -- a compile-time\n\"insurance policy\". Each capture is a Declaration (name + is_mut);\nthe block stays inline at runtime, so the only effect is the typer's\nscope-restriction check. Child 0 is the Body.NodeTypeAST node kind. Each variant carries an optional payload (struct, string, bool).ExprAST expression node with line/col, type, children, and node-specific payload.Expr.deleteNull-safe delete. The auto-generated version dereferences `self`\nunconditionally, so the asap pass deleting an owned-but-null Expr\n(e.g. a fold helper that returns NULL on failure) SEGVs. Guarding\nhere lets functions return owned `Expr` that may be null without\nthe caller having to clone-and-leak to dodge the deep delete.Expr.errorPrint a diagnostic error with file path and source location.Expr.todo_errorLike error() but adds \"not implemented yet\" note.Expr.lang_errorLike error() but adds \"bug in the language\" note.Expr.add_childTake ownership of `child` and append it to the children list.Expr.push_child_cloneClone `child` and append the clone to the children list.Expr.take_childrenAppend other's children into self via raw memcpy (no cloning).\nZeroes other's count so it no longer owns the moved items.Expr.newCreate a new Expr with the given node_type and source location.Map__I64_Str.newCreate an empty Map of the types provided for the key and values respectively.\nThe key type must implement `cmp`.Map__I64_Str.clearDrop all live keys and values but keep the allocated storage so the Map can be reused.Map__I64_Str.key_ptrRef to the key slot at sorted index `i`. Unchecked: callers\nguarantee `i < self.keys.count` (Map's binary-search consumers\nalways validate before calling). Bypasses Vec.get's throwing\nbounds check.Map__I64_Str.val_ptrRef to the value slot at sorted index `i`. Same caller-validated\ncontract as key_ptr.Map__I64_Str.hasTrue if a value exists for the given key.Map__I64_Str.getReturn a ref to the value for `key`. Throws KeyNotFound if\n`key` is absent; call as `map.get(k)!` (or `map[k]`) to panic\non a missing key.Map__I64_Str.setInsert or overwrite the value for `key`. The value is owned.Vec__Bool.newCreate a new empty Vec for elements of type T.Vec__Bool.clearDrop all live elements via elem_delete but keep the allocated\nstorage and element-type metadata so the Vec can be reused.Vec__Bool.pushAppend an element to the end. `val` is owned: after this call the\ncaller must not use the value passed -- clone it first if needed.Vec__Bool.appendConsume the contents of `other` by appending them to `self`.\n`other` is taken by ownership and will be empty after the call.Vec__Bool.move_fromReplace self's contents with other's via memcpy (no per-elem clone).\nAvoids the Vec_clone + extra Vec_delete that plain `self = other` emits.\nTakes `mut` (not `own`) so caller retains ownership of other; its\nnatural scope-end auto-delete frees other.data. Setting other.count = 0\nprevents that auto-delete from re-running elem_delete on items whose\nbytes were moved into self.Vec__Bool.getReturn a reference to the element at index `i`. Throws\nOutOfBounds if `i` is past the end; call as `vec[i]`\nto panic on a bad index. The reference is valid until the\nnext mutation.Vec__Bool.popRemove and return the last element. Panics if empty. The caller\ntakes ownership of the returned value.Vec__Bool.take_prefixSplit off the first `n` elements into a new Vec. Panics if `n`\nexceeds self.len(). The remaining elements shift to the front.Vec__Bool.setOverwrite the element at index `i`. `val` is owned. Throws\nOutOfBounds if `i` is past the end; call as `vec[i] = val`\n(or `vec.set(i, own val)!`) to panic on a bad index.Vec__Bool.push_takeMove bytes of src[i] into self (push). Source slot is zeroed so that\nsrc's eventual elem_delete on it is a no-op (relies on the same\ncount==0/data==NULL convention used by take_children and Vec.delete).Vec__Bool.deleteDrop each element via elem_delete, free storage, then free self\nunless `call_free` is false.Vec__Bool.cloneDeep-copy the Vec and all its elements via elem_clone.Vec__FieldLayout.newCreate a new empty Vec for elements of type T.Vec__FieldLayout.clearDrop all live elements via elem_delete but keep the allocated\nstorage and element-type metadata so the Vec can be reused.Vec__FieldLayout.pushAppend an element to the end. `val` is owned: after this call the\ncaller must not use the value passed -- clone it first if needed.Vec__FieldLayout.appendConsume the contents of `other` by appending them to `self`.\n`other` is taken by ownership and will be empty after the call.Vec__FieldLayout.move_fromReplace self's contents with other's via memcpy (no per-elem clone).\nAvoids the Vec_clone + extra Vec_delete that plain `self = other` emits.\nTakes `mut` (not `own`) so caller retains ownership of other; its\nnatural scope-end auto-delete frees other.data. Setting other.count = 0\nprevents that auto-delete from re-running elem_delete on items whose\nbytes were moved into self.Vec__FieldLayout.getReturn a reference to the element at index `i`. Throws\nOutOfBounds if `i` is past the end; call as `vec[i]`\nto panic on a bad index. The reference is valid until the\nnext mutation.Vec__FieldLayout.popRemove and return the last element. Panics if empty. The caller\ntakes ownership of the returned value.Vec__FieldLayout.take_prefixSplit off the first `n` elements into a new Vec. Panics if `n`\nexceeds self.len(). The remaining elements shift to the front.Vec__FieldLayout.setOverwrite the element at index `i`. `val` is owned. Throws\nOutOfBounds if `i` is past the end; call as `vec[i] = val`\n(or `vec.set(i, own val)!`) to panic on a bad index.Vec__FieldLayout.push_takeMove bytes of src[i] into self (push). Source slot is zeroed so that\nsrc's eventual elem_delete on it is a no-op (relies on the same\ncount==0/data==NULL convention used by take_children and Vec.delete).Vec__FieldLayout.deleteDrop each element via elem_delete, free storage, then free self\nunless `call_free` is false.Vec__FieldLayout.cloneDeep-copy the Vec and all its elements via elem_clone.Vec__Declaration.newCreate a new empty Vec for elements of type T.Vec__Declaration.clearDrop all live elements via elem_delete but keep the allocated\nstorage and element-type metadata so the Vec can be reused.Vec__Declaration.pushAppend an element to the end. `val` is owned: after this call the\ncaller must not use the value passed -- clone it first if needed.Vec__Declaration.appendConsume the contents of `other` by appending them to `self`.\n`other` is taken by ownership and will be empty after the call.Vec__Declaration.move_fromReplace self's contents with other's via memcpy (no per-elem clone).\nAvoids the Vec_clone + extra Vec_delete that plain `self = other` emits.\nTakes `mut` (not `own`) so caller retains ownership of other; its\nnatural scope-end auto-delete frees other.data. Setting other.count = 0\nprevents that auto-delete from re-running elem_delete on items whose\nbytes were moved into self.Vec__Declaration.getReturn a reference to the element at index `i`. Throws\nOutOfBounds if `i` is past the end; call as `vec[i]`\nto panic on a bad index. The reference is valid until the\nnext mutation.Vec__Declaration.popRemove and return the last element. Panics if empty. The caller\ntakes ownership of the returned value.Vec__Declaration.take_prefixSplit off the first `n` elements into a new Vec. Panics if `n`\nexceeds self.len(). The remaining elements shift to the front.Vec__Declaration.setOverwrite the element at index `i`. `val` is owned. Throws\nOutOfBounds if `i` is past the end; call as `vec[i] = val`\n(or `vec.set(i, own val)!`) to panic on a bad index.Vec__Declaration.push_takeMove bytes of src[i] into self (push). Source slot is zeroed so that\nsrc's eventual elem_delete on it is a no-op (relies on the same\ncount==0/data==NULL convention used by take_children and Vec.delete).Vec__Declaration.deleteDrop each element via elem_delete, free storage, then free self\nunless `call_free` is false.Vec__Declaration.cloneDeep-copy the Vec and all its elements via elem_clone.Vec__Expr.newCreate a new empty Vec for elements of type T.Vec__Expr.clearDrop all live elements via elem_delete but keep the allocated\nstorage and element-type metadata so the Vec can be reused.Vec__Expr.pushAppend an element to the end. `val` is owned: after this call the\ncaller must not use the value passed -- clone it first if needed.Vec__Expr.appendConsume the contents of `other` by appending them to `self`.\n`other` is taken by ownership and will be empty after the call.Vec__Expr.move_fromReplace self's contents with other's via memcpy (no per-elem clone).\nAvoids the Vec_clone + extra Vec_delete that plain `self = other` emits.\nTakes `mut` (not `own`) so caller retains ownership of other; its\nnatural scope-end auto-delete frees other.data. Setting other.count = 0\nprevents that auto-delete from re-running elem_delete on items whose\nbytes were moved into self.Vec__Expr.getReturn a reference to the element at index `i`. Throws\nOutOfBounds if `i` is past the end; call as `vec[i]`\nto panic on a bad index. The reference is valid until the\nnext mutation.Vec__Expr.popRemove and return the last element. Panics if empty. The caller\ntakes ownership of the returned value.Vec__Expr.take_prefixSplit off the first `n` elements into a new Vec. Panics if `n`\nexceeds self.len(). The remaining elements shift to the front.Vec__Expr.setOverwrite the element at index `i`. `val` is owned. Throws\nOutOfBounds if `i` is past the end; call as `vec[i] = val`\n(or `vec.set(i, own val)!`) to panic on a bad index.Vec__Expr.push_takeMove bytes of src[i] into self (push). Source slot is zeroed so that\nsrc's eventual elem_delete on it is a no-op (relies on the same\ncount==0/data==NULL convention used by take_children and Vec.delete).Vec__Expr.deleteDrop each element via elem_delete, free storage, then free self\nunless `call_free` is false.Vec__Expr.cloneDeep-copy the Vec and all its elements via elem_clone.Vec__I64.newCreate a new empty Vec for elements of type T.Vec__I64.clearDrop all live elements via elem_delete but keep the allocated\nstorage and element-type metadata so the Vec can be reused.Vec__I64.pushAppend an element to the end. `val` is owned: after this call the\ncaller must not use the value passed -- clone it first if needed.Vec__I64.appendConsume the contents of `other` by appending them to `self`.\n`other`