ed registry blobs to\nthe runtime. Not intended for direct user calls.helpPrint the doc comment and the kind/signature info for a top-level\ndeclaration or struct/enum member (`Type.method`). When both are\nregistered, print the doc first then the info. If neither is\nregistered print \"undefined symbol: <name>\".TupleHeterogeneous sequence of values with mixed types.Tuple.newCreate an empty Tuple.Tuple.push_type_nameInternal helper that keeps tuple metadata as string type names.Tuple.pushAppend a value of the given type. `val` is owned.Tuple.getRef to element at index `i`. Panics if out of bounds.Tuple.type_atType name of the element at index `i`. Panics if `i` is past\nthe end.Tuple.size_atByte size of the element at index `i`. Panics if `i` is past\nthe end.Vec__U32.newCreate a new empty Vec for elements of type T.Vec__U32.clearDrop all live elements via elem_delete but keep the allocated\nstorage and element-type metadata so the Vec can be reused.Vec__U32.pushAppend an element to the end. `val` is owned: after this call the\ncaller must not use the value passed -- clone it first if needed.Vec__U32.appendConsume the contents of `other` by appending them to `self`.\n`other` is taken by ownership and will be empty after the call.Vec__U32.move_fromReplace self's contents with other's via memcpy (no per-elem clone).\nAvoids the Vec_clone + extra Vec_delete that plain `self = other` emits.\nTakes `mut` (not `own`) so caller retains ownership of other; its\nnatural scope-end auto-delete frees other.data. Setting other.count = 0\nprevents that auto-delete from re-running elem_delete on items whose\nbytes were moved into self.Vec__U32.getReturn a reference to the element at index `i`. Throws\nOutOfBounds if `i` is past the end; call as `vec[i]`\nto panic on a bad index. The reference is valid until the\nnext mutation.Vec__U32.popRemove and return the last element. Panics if empty. The caller\ntakes ownership of the returned value.Vec__U32.take_prefixSplit off the first `n` elements into a new Vec. Panics if `n`\nexceeds self.len(). The remaining elements shift to the front.Vec__U32.setOverwrite the element at index `i`. `val` is owned. Throws\nOutOfBounds if `i` is past the end; call as `vec[i] = val`\n(or `vec.set(i, own val)!`) to panic on a bad index.Vec__U32.push_takeMove bytes of src[i] into self (push). Source slot is zeroed so that\nsrc's eventual elem_delete on it is a no-op (relies on the same\ncount==0/data==NULL convention used by take_children and Vec.delete).Vec__U32.deleteDrop each element via elem_delete, free storage, then free self\nunless `call_free` is false.Vec__U32.cloneDeep-copy the Vec and all its elements via elem_clone.KwargsMapString-keyed map of dynamically-typed kwargs values.KwargsMap.newCreate an empty KwargsMap.KwargsMap.hasTrue if `key` exists in the map.KwargsMap.setInsert or overwrite `key` with typed value. The value is owned.KwargsMap.getRef to the value stored under `key`. Panics if not found.KwargsMap.type_atType name of the value stored under `key`.KwargsMap.size_atByte size of the value stored under `key`.Map__Str_Tuple.newCreate an empty Map of the types provided for the key and values respectively.\nThe key type must implement `cmp`.Map__Str_Tuple.clearDrop all live keys and values but keep the allocated storage so the Map can be reused.Map__Str_Tuple.key_ptrRef to the key slot at sorted index `i`. Unchecked: callers\nguarantee `i < self.keys.count` (Map's binary-search consumers\nalways validate before calling). Bypasses Vec.get's throwing\nbounds check.Map__Str_Tuple.val_ptrRef to the value slot at sorted index `i`. Same caller-validated\ncontract as key_ptr.Map__Str_Tuple.hasTrue if a value exists for the given key.Map__Str_Tuple.getReturn a ref to the value for `key`. Throws KeyNotFound if\n`key` is absent; call as `map.get(k)!` (or `map[k]`) to panic\non a missing key.Map__Str_Tuple.setInsert or overwrite the value for `key`. The value is owned.Vec__Tuple.newCreate a new empty Vec for elements of type T.Vec__Tuple.clearDrop all live elements via elem_delete but keep the allocated\nstorage and element-type metadata so the Vec can be reused.Vec__Tuple.pushAppend an element to the end. `val` is owned: after this call the\ncaller must not use the value passed -- clone it first if needed.Vec__Tuple.appendConsume the contents of `other` by appending them to `self`.\n`other` is taken by ownership and will be empty after the call.Vec__Tuple.move_fromReplace self's contents with other's via memcpy (no per-elem clone).\nAvoids the Vec_clone + extra Vec_delete that plain `self = other` emits.\nTakes `mut` (not `own`) so caller retains ownership of other; its\nnatural scope-end auto-delete frees other.data. Setting other.count = 0\nprevents that auto-delete from re-running elem_delete on items whose\nbytes were moved into self.Vec__Tuple.getReturn a reference to the element at index `i`. Throws\nOutOfBounds if `i` is past the end; call as `vec[i]`\nto panic on a bad index. The reference is valid until the\nnext mutation.Vec__Tuple.popRemove and return the last element. Panics if empty. The caller\ntakes ownership of the returned value.Vec__Tuple.take_prefixSplit off the first `n` elements into a new Vec. Panics if `n`\nexceeds self.len(). The remaining elements shift to the front.Vec__Tuple.setOverwrite the element at index `i`. `val` is owned. Throws\nOutOfBounds if `i` is past the end; call as `vec[i] = val`\n(or `vec.set(i, own val)!`) to panic on a bad index.Vec__Tuple.push_takeMove bytes of src[i] into self (push). Source slot is zeroed so that\nsrc's eventual elem_delete on it is a no-op (relies on the same\ncount==0/data==NULL convention used by take_children and Vec.delete).Vec__Tuple.deleteDrop each element via elem_delete, free storage, then free self\nunless `call_free` is false.Vec__Tuple.cloneDeep-copy the Vec and all its elements via elem_clone.printlnPrint strings to stdout followed by a newline.printPrint strings to stdout without a newline.FileFile handle for reading or writing on disk.File.newOpen a file at `path` for reading or writing.File.updateOpen a file at `path` for in-place update: reads and writes are\nboth allowed and the cursor can be moved with `seek`, so small\nregions can be patched without rewriting the whole file. The file\nmust already exist.File.writeWrite a string to the file and return `self` so writes chain via\nUFCS: `f.write(\"a\").write(\"b\").write(\"c\")`. Panics unless opened\nfor writing or update.File.read_allRead the entire file contents into a Str. Panics if opened\nwrite-only.File.readRead up to `count` bytes starting at the current cursor position\nand advance the cursor. The result is shorter than `count` near\nend-of-file. Panics if opened write-only.File.tellReturn the current cursor position as a byte offset from the start\nof the file.File.seekMove the cursor to an absolute byte offset from the start of the\nfile. Returns `self` so calls chain via UFCS.File.seek_curMove the cursor by `delta` bytes relative to its current position\n(`delta` may be negative). Returns `self` so calls chain via UFCS.File.seek_endMove the cursor to `delta` bytes relative to the end of the file\n(`delta` is typically <= 0). `f.seek_end(0)` followed by `f.tell()`\nyields the file size. Returns `self` so calls chain via UFCS.File.closeClose the underlying file handle and NULL it. Private: invoked\nonly from `delete`, which the garbager inserts after a File\nlocal's last use.File.deleteRelease the File: close the handle, then free the struct shell\nunless the caller still owns it (`call_free = false` for a\nstack/value local). The garbager inserts this call right after the\nFile's last use.UPtrUPtr is the target-native unsigned integer for raw pointer arithmetic,\naddress calculations, and byte counts that must match pointer width.\nThe source alias defaults to U64; the loader retargets it to U32 for\n32-bit targets before typecheck/codegen.RangeInteger interval from start (inclusive) to end (exclusive).Range.newCreate a Range from `start` (inclusive) to `end` (exclusive).Range.getThe i-th value in the range (start+i or start-i for reverse).SetUnordered collection of unique typed elements.U16Unsigned 16-bit integer.U16.to_strConvert to decimal string representation.U16.unityReturn the multiplicative identity (1) for this type.U16.distanceAbsolute difference between two values, useful for Range iteration.U16.safe_addAddition that throws IntegerOverflow on unsigned wrap.\nUse U16.add for the wrapping variant.U16.safe_subSubtraction that throws IntegerOverflow when a < b (underflow\nwraps unsigned). Use U16.sub for the wrapping variant.U16.safe_mulMultiplication that throws IntegerOverflow on unsigned wrap.\nUse U16.mul for the wrapping variant.